    {
      "name": "Inventor Dedication",
      "type": "feat",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>You become trained in Crafting and inventor class DC. You gain the Inventor skill feat. Choose an innovation (Weapon Innovation — Katana). You gain that innovation, though you don't gain other abilities that modify it such as modifications or Explode.</p>"
        },
        "featType": { "value": "archetype" },
        "level": { "value": 2 },
        "traits": { "value": ["archetype", "dedication"] },
        "prerequisites": { "value": [{ "value": "Intelligence 14" }] }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Explosion (Inventor Archetype)",
      "type": "feat",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>You gain the Explode action. You intentionally take your innovation beyond normal safety limits, dealing 2d6 fire damage (+ 1d6 per level above 1st, so 16d6 at level 15) in a 5-foot emanation. Basic Reflex save vs your inventor class DC. Unstable: DC 13 flat check (Legendary Crafting) or innovation malfunctions.</p>"
        },
        "featType": { "value": "archetype" },
        "level": { "value": 6 },
        "traits": { "value": ["archetype"] },
        "prerequisites": { "value": [{ "value": "Basic Breakthrough" }] }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Explode",
      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>You intentionally take Theorem (your Innovation) beyond normal safety limits. All creatures in a 5-foot emanation take <strong>16d6 fire damage</strong> (basic Reflex save vs Inventor Class DC). Unstable: Attempt DC 13 flat check (Legendary Crafting) after applying effects. On failure, innovation can't be used for further unstable actions until 10 minutes of retuning. On critical failure, take fire damage equal to half your level (8).</p><p>If you have Revolutionary Innovation: choose 5-ft, 10-ft, or 15-ft emanation.</p>"
        },
        "actionType": { "value": "action" },
        "actions": { "value": 2 },
        "traits": { "value": ["unstable", "inventor", "fire", "manipulate"] },
        "requirements": { "value": "Theorem (innovation weapon) is held" }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Attack of Opportunity",
      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Reaction.webp",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature within your reach uses a manipulate action or a move action, makes a ranged attack, or leaves a square during a move action it's using.<br>Make a melee Strike against the triggering creature. If the attack hits and the trigger was a manipulate action, disrupt that action. This Strike doesn't count toward your multiple attack penalty, and your multiple attack penalty doesn't apply to this Strike.</p>"
        },
        "actionType": { "value": "reaction" },
        "actions": { "value": null },
        "traits": { "value": ["fighter"] }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Draconic Breath (Sonic Cone)",
      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>Lisa exhales a keening wail of focused sonic energy in a 30-foot cone. Creatures in the area take sonic damage (scales with level — see Battlezoo rules for exact value). Basic Reflex save vs your class DC or spell DC. Recharge: Once per 1d4 rounds (or per the Battlezoo rules for your level).</p><p><em>The emerald dragon's breath is a precisely tuned resonance, not a roar — a frequency calculated to shatter armor plating and stun nervous systems.</em></p>"
        },
        "actionType": { "value": "action" },
        "actions": { "value": 2 },
        "traits": { "value": ["sonic", "dragon", "evocation", "arcane"] }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Specialty Crafting (Weapons)",
      "type": "feat",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>Your background as an artisan gives you exceptional crafting ability. When you Craft items of a particular type (weapons), you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your Crafting checks, and you reduce the number of days to Craft by 1 (min 1).</p>"
        },
        "featType": { "value": "skill" },
        "level": { "value": 1 },
        "traits": { "value": ["general", "skill"] },
        "prerequisites": { "value": [{ "value": "trained in Crafting" }] }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Combat Flexibility",
      "type": "feat",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>Through constant refinement, you're prepared for any combat. During your daily preparations, you can gain one fighter feat of 8th level or lower that you don't already have. You can use that feat until your next daily preparations.</p>"
        },
        "featType": { "value": "class" },
        "level": { "value": 15 },
        "traits": { "value": ["fighter"] },
        "prerequisites": { "value": [] }
      }
    }
